page.title: 01Totteridge and Penn, Bucks.
page.content: {High Wycombe}is{North West}of{London. The distance from{High Wycombe}to the centre of{London}is 50km. Our area is to the{East}of{High Wycombe}extending from{Totteridge}in the{West}to{Penn}in the{East.}In the land around{High {Wycombe}the ground has flint and chalk in it. Lots of the old houses are built of flint. There are a lot of furniture factories around{High {Wycombe}because we have lots of Beech woodland. People called Bodgers used to work in the woods making chairs. Around{High Wycombe}are the{Chiltern {Hills.}If we look out of our classroom window we can look across the valley where we can see lots of farmland and woodland. In{High Wycombe}are people from many different countries such as {Poland, India, Africa,}the{Caribbean and many others.
